{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17528331","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17528331"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:41:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:41:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14288"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14288","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14288"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.22,0.09,0.14,0.24,0.31]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6983"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106076"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6983","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6983"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14288"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88551"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"15"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1086"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"2132"},{"type":"tags","id":"2142"},{"type":"tags","id":"2918"},{"type":"tags","id":"4487"},{"type":"tags","id":"4969"},{"type":"tags","id":"4991"},{"type":"tags","id":"11622"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"12756"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"16472"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38794"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38795"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43516"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45033"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106076","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/106076"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 55-year-old Indigenous female is referred to Renal Clinic with a two-week history of swollen legs and frothy urine. She has a medical history of hypertension and takes irbesartan and amlodipine. On examination, she appears unwell. Her pulse rate is 78/min, blood pressure 149/88 mmHg, respiratory rate 20/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. She has pitting oedema to the level of the groin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInvestigations reveal:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUrinalysis: 3+ protein\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESerum albumin: 20 g/L (35-50)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETotal cholesterol: 7.2 mmol/L (2.0-5.5)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESerum creatinine: 130 \u03bcmol/L (60-110)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERenal biopsy light microscopy: Focal segmental glomerulosclerosis (FSGS)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EElectron microscopy: Diffuse foot process effacement\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHigh-dose oral prednisolone is commenced. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medications should also be commenced?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Benzathine benzylpenicillin","Insulin aspart (short-acting)","Insulin protaphane (intermediate-acting)","Risedronate","Trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has been diagnosed with focal segmental glomerulosclerosis (FSGS) based on renal biopsy findings. The nephrologist has recommended high-dose oral prednisolone, which is a first-line treatment for FSGS presentations with nephrotic syndrome. When starting high-dose corticosteroids, it is important to consider prophylactic medications to prevent complications associated with steroid use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETrimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole\u003C/strong\u003E (Bactrim) is crucial for Pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia (PJP) prophylaxis in patients on high-dose immunosuppression. PJP can be a life-threatening complication in immunosuppressed patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBenzathine benzylpenicillin\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. It is used to treat bacterial infections including group A Streptococcus which is associated with acute rheumatic fever, a condition with a higher prevalence in Indigenous Australians.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInsulin aspart (short-acting) \u003C/strong\u003Eand \u003Cstrong\u003EInsulin protaphane (intermediate-acting)\u003C/strong\u003E are both incorrect. Steroids can certainly cause hyperglycaemia, although it would be inappropriate to start insulin immediately without a period of BSL monitoring first. Insulin protaphane is often used as the peak action typically matches the afternoon hyperglycaemia peak associated with steroid use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERisedronate\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Whilst high-dose steroid use is a risk factor for osteoporosis, it would be inappropriate to prophylactically commence anti-resorptive therapy. Some clinicians may commence patients in high risk groups on prophylactic colecalciferol +/- calcium supplementation whilst on high-dose steroids.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["High-dose oral prednisolone is a first-line treatment for primary focal segmental glomerulosclerosis (FSGS) presenting with nephrotic syndrome.","Prophylactic medications are important when commencing high-dose corticosteroids to prevent complications.","Pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia (PJP) prophylaxis with trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole is crucial in immunosuppressed patients."],"references":["Moghadam-Kia S, Werth VP. Prevention and treatment of systemic glucocorticoid side effects. In: StatPearls [online]. 2010. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2872100/","Davis J. Prevention of opportunistic infections in immunosuppressed patients in the tropical Top End of the Northern Territory of Australia. The Department of Health and Aged Care; 2003 Dec 3;27(4). Available at: https://www1.health.gov.au/internet/main/publishing.nsf/Content/cda-pubs-cdi-2003-cdi2704-htm-cdi2704s.htm"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88551"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14288"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88551","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/88551"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-15T20:51:20+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-15T20:51:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6983"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106076"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"15","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/15"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd54","name":"Nephrology","synonyms":["Renal"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:52:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"78","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/78"},"attributes":{"emoji